com.upsight.android.managedvariables.experience

Interface UpsightUserExperience.Handler

  • Enclosing class:
    UpsightUserExperience

    public static interface UpsightUserExperience.Handler
    Handler interface for user experience bundles.

    The application will not receive UpsightUserExperience.Handler callbacks if the device has no network connectivity.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Called when a new user experience bundle is received.

    • Method Detail

      • onReceive

        boolean onReceive()
        Called when a new user experience bundle is received. The return value is used to signal whether to apply the new experience.
        Returns:
        true to apply the new user experience bundle; false to skip.

      • onSynchronize

        void onSynchronize(java.util.List<java.lang.String> tags)
        Called when the user experience bundle is synchronized. If onReceive() returned true, synchronization means all the UpsightManagedVariables will provide values that are in-sync with the server-set user experience for this user. If onReceive() returned false, onSynchronize(List) will still be called but the UpsightManagedVariables will return locally-persisted values that may be out-of-sync with server configurations.
        Parameters:
        tags - The list of UpsightManagedVariable tags modified by a new user experience bundle. If no new user experience bundle is applied, either because the local values are already up-to-date, or a new bundle is skipped, this list will be empty.
